race.comment: DEEBEE'S GIRL (2) returned in good order and fourth-up today. Stretches out to this trip for the first time this campaign after fading late when fourth over 1005m at Taree. Assess on her dominant win here two runs back. Leading prospect. FELASUVI (5) chipped away late at her first run back with an even fifth over 1005m at Taree. Will relish the claim and the step up in trip. Expected to take a hand in the finish. HIGHLAND MIRAGE (4) back to his right distance range after struggling to run the mile out when a plugging eighth at Coffs Harbour. Kept fresh and looks well weighted from the low draw. Each way. THE AMBASSADOR (3) lightly raced mare with ability. Comes back in trip after she gripped on late for a handy third over 1600m at Inverell. Maps well and stays in the calculations.
